com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec

Interface FieldEntry


  • public interface FieldEntry
    An entry for a UPA FieldList that can house any DataTypes including primitive types, set-defined types, or container types. If updating information, when the FieldEntry contains a primitive type, it replaces any previously stored or displayed data associated with the same fieldId. If the FieldEntry contains another container type, action values associated with that type indicate how to modify the information.
    See Also:
    FieldList

    • Method Detail

      • clear

        void clear()
        Clears FieldEntry object. Useful for object reuse during encoding. While decoding, FieldEntry object can be reused without using clear().

      • encode

        int encode(EncodeIterator iter)
        Encodes a FieldEntry from pre-encoded data. This method expects the same EncodeIterator that was used with FieldList.encodeInit(EncodeIterator, LocalFieldSetDefDb, int). You must properly populate fieldId() and dataType() Set encodedData with pre-encoded data before calling this method. Typical use:
        1. Call FieldList.encodeInit()
        2. Call FieldEntry.encode() for each field in the list using the same buffer
        3. Call FieldList.encodeComplete()
        Parameters:
        iter - The encoder iterator.
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
        See Also:
        EncodeIterator

        Deprecated. as of ETAJ3.0.0.L1. Similar, but more type safe, functionality is provided by other FieldEntry interfaces
        Encodes a field within a list. The field data must cast to a primitive type. Typical use:

        2. Call FieldEntry.encode() for each field in the list using the same buffer
        3. Call FieldList.encodeComplete()
        Parameters:
        iter - The encoder iterator.
        data - The data to be encoded (must cast to a primitive type or an error is returned).

      • encodeInit

        int encodeInit(EncodeIterator iter,
               int encodingMaxSize)
        Encodes a FieldEntry from a complex type, such as a container type or an array. Used to put aggregate fields, such as element lists into a field list. Typical use:
        1. Call encodeInit()
        2. Call one or more encoding methods for the complex type using the same buffer
        3. Call encodeComplete()
        Parameters:
        iter - The encoder iterator.
        encodingMaxSize - Max encoding size for field entry (If Unknown set to zero).
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
        See Also:
        EncodeIterator

      • encodeComplete

        int encodeComplete(EncodeIterator iter,
                   boolean success)
        Completes encoding a FieldEntry for a complex type. Typical use:
        1. Call encodeInit()
        2. Call one or more encoding methods for the complex type using the same buffer
        3. Call encodeComplete()
        Parameters:
        iter - The encoder iterator.
        success - If true - successfully complete the aggregate, if false - remove the aggregate from the buffer.
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
        See Also:
        EncodeIterator

      • fieldId

        void fieldId(int fieldId)
        The field identifier. Refers to specific name and type information defined by an external field dictionary, such as the RDMFieldDictionary. Negative fieldId values typically refer to user defined values while positive fieldId values typically refer to Thomson Reuters defined values. Must be in the range of -32768 - 32767.
        Parameters:
        fieldId - the fieldId to set

      • fieldId

        int fieldId()
        The field identifier. Refers to specific name and type information defined by an external field dictionary, such as the RDMFieldDictionary. Negative fieldId values typically refer to user defined values while positive fieldId values typically refer to Thomson Reuters defined values.
        Returns:
        the fieldId

      • dataType

        void dataType(int dataType)
        The field's data type. dataType must be from the DataTypes enumeration. Must be in the range of DataTypes.INT - 255.
        Parameters:
        dataType - the dataType to set

      • dataType

        int dataType()
        The field's data type. While decoding, if dataType is DataTypes.UNKNOWN, the user must determine the type of contained information from the associated field dictionary. If set-defined data is used, dataType will indicate specific DataTypes information as indicated by the set definition.
        Returns:
        the dataType
